[1] Ukraine (Vinnytsia)
Date: Tue 2 Oct 2018 12:15 EEST
Source: 112UA [edited]
https://112.international/society/measles-outbreak-in-ukraine-28-children-get-sick-in-vinnytsia-region-32759.html


Since the beginning of September [2018], 28 children got sick with measles in one of the Vinnytsia region schools. Tetiana Bondarenko, the head of disease treatment and prevention for children of Health Department of Vinnytsia Regional State Administration claimed this as BBC Ukraine reported.

The measles outbreak is connected with the fact that the parents refuse the vaccination. According to Bondarenko, all the sick children were not vaccinated or did not have the follow-up vaccination. "In the region, there are enough vaccines for the children's protective vaccination coverage," she noted.

It is reported that the incidence of measles in Vinnytsia region increased since the beginning of a school year. 83 cases of the measles, including 71 cases involving children were spotted in the region during a week. Earlier it was reported that as of 12 Sep 2018, 30 744 persons have been sickened with measles since the beginning of 2018.

Earlier Moldova imposed the "orange" threat level on the results of the session of the national emergency commission for public health. It is noted that most of the cases were spotted in the southern regions of Moldova. Also, the European Health Security Agency reported that, in Europe, only Romania and Italy had reported more people infected with measles in 2017 [2017 or 2018? - Mod.SH] than Ukraine.

