******
[2] Ukraine (Lviv): fatal
Date: Tue 2 Oct 2018 17:44 EEST
Source: 112 UA [edited]
https://112.international/ukraine-top-news/3-year-old-child-dies-due-to-measles-in-lviv-region-32779.html


On 1 Oct 2018, in Lviv regional infectious hospital, a 3 year old boy died due to measles. Natalya Tymko, the epidemiologist of this hospital claimed this as ZAXID.NET reported. It is stated that a boy lived at Zhovkva district of Lviv region and was hospitalized 2 weeks ago. The disease caused the complication in the form of the inflammation in the brain (encephalitis). The doctors could not save the child.

Oleg Kogut, the director of Lviv regional lab, center claimed that the boy was vaccinated against measles. It is the 2nd death of a child in Lviv region this year [2018]. In April, a 3 year old girl died from complications of measles.

Lviv region is a leader in the number of the people sickened with measles, 6310 cases, including 1964 adults and 4346 children, were infected. The 2nd place is occupied by Zakarpattia with 3126 cases.

